@8700 = ~Slayer Form~
@8701 = ~Slayer Form

Manifest your savage compulsions, taking on the form of the brutal essence of Bhaal: a violent, powerful creature made of teeth and claws.

The Slayer form grants the following benefits:

– Strength and Dexterity set to 21 (23 at 3 million XP or more, 25 at 6 million XP or more)
– Constitution increased by 3
– Attacks per round set to 3 (7/2 at 3 million XP or more, 4 at 6 million XP or more)
– Basic claw and teeth attacks deal 1d8+3 crushing/slashing damage plus +1 cold damage with a +5 THAC0 bonus, acts as a +5 weapon. At 3 million XP or more, the damage increases to 2d4+5, and the cold damage to 1d2+1. At 6 million XP or more, the damage increases to 2d4+6, the cold damage to 1d3+1, and the THAC0 bonus to +6.
– All attack hits as if they were +6 magical weapons for the purposes of overcoming weapon immunities
– Deals 2d6 extra crushing and slashing damage to targets that are knocked down, unconscious, or otherwise disabled
– Movement speed increased by a factor of 5
– Effective AC set to -10
– Saving throws improve by 5
– Magic Resistance increases by 20%
– THAC0 set to 0
– Fully healed upon transforming
– 100 Hit Points, 150 at XP of 3 million or more, and 200 HP at XP of 6 million or more. If maximum Hit Points are higher, they increase by 15 instead
– Immunity to imprisonment, level drain, stun, fear, panic, morale failure, and missile attacks

This form is unstable and must sate its thirst for blood to maintain it. A kill must occur once per turn to maintain it, otherwise, the user will be forced back into their normal shape. It will nevertheless force the user to transform back into their normal shape after 2 hours.~

@8702 = ~Let the Slaughter Begin~
@8703 = ~Let the Slaughter Begin
Scream like a ravenous beast, imprinting a sinister mark on nearby creatures, which makes their deaths strengthen your defenses and fury. Marked enemies must save vs. Death at -2 or be stunned for 2 rounds. If a marked enemy dies within 4 rounds, you gain a +1 bonus to Armor Class, Damage, and THAC0 for 4 rounds. The mark itself cannot be resisted.~

@8704 = ~Relentless Lunge~
@8705 = ~Relentless Lunge
Drive the target to the ground for 1 round if they fail a save vs. Death at -4, dealing 2d6+1 crushing damage. At 3 million XP or higher, the damage increases to 4d6+2.~

@8706 = ~Sumptuous Blood Bath~
@8707 = ~Sumptuous Blood Bath
Slash open a foe's arteries, instantly dealing 2d8+4 slashing damage (halved if they save vs. Death at -4). The target then bleeds for 3 rounds, taking 2 slashing damage each round. Each time the target bleeds, the Slayer is drenched in blood and heals 2d6 hit points. At 3 million XP or more, the initial damage increases to 3d8+6 slashing, the bleeding to 2 slashing twice per round, and the healing to 3d6 hit points. If the save is made, the Slayer only heals once.~

@8800 = ~SINGLE-WEAPON: This fighting style is for characters who do not wish to use a shield but want some bonus when using a one-handed melee weapon.

No skill (0 slots): The wielder suffers a -1 penalty to Speed Factor.

Proficient (1 slot): The wielder gains a +1 bonus to damage rolls, Armor Class, and Speed Factor. Attacks score critical hits on rolls of 19 or 20.

Specialized (2 slots): The wielder gains a +2 bonus to damage rolls, Armor Class, and Speed Factor. Attacks score critical hits on rolls of 19 or 20.~

@8801 = ~SWORD AND SHIELD: Anyone can pick up a shield and get its basic protection bonuses, but by spending slots on this fighting style, an adventurer can maximize the benefits received.

No skill (0 slots): The wielder suffers a -1 penalty to all combat rolls and a -1 penalty to Armor Class against missile attacks.

Proficient (1 slot): The wielder no longer suffers these penalties and gains a +1 bonus to Armor Class against missile attacks.

Specialized (2 slots): The wielder gains a +1 bonus to Armor Class and an additional +2 bonus to Armor Class against missile attacks.

NOTE: Despite the name of this style, any one-handed melee weapon in combination with a shield will receive the aforementioned bonuses.~

@8802 = ~TWO-HANDED: This fighting style allows the character to use a two-handed melee weapon and receive special bonuses.

No skill (0 slots): The wielder suffers a -1 penalty to Armor Class.

Proficient (1 slot): The wielder no longer suffers Armor Class penalties and gains a +1 bonus to damage rolls and Speed Factor.

Specialized (2 slots): The wielder gains a +2 bonus to damage rolls, a +4 bonus to Speed Factor, and can score critical hits on attack rolls of 19 or 20 when using two-handed weapons.

NOTE: Magical two-handed weapons are more powerful than their single-handed counterparts. This counterbalances the fact that you can't use a second weapon or shield when using a two-handed weapon. The Holy Avenger and Vorpal Sword are examples of weapons that are two-handed.~

@8803 = ~TWO-WEAPON: This fighting style allows the character to use two melee weapons at the same time with fewer penalties.

No skill (0 slots): When wielding two weapons without proficiency, the character suffers a -2 penalty to Armor Class, a -1 penalty to damage rolls with the main weapon (-2 with the off-hand), and a -4 penalty to THAC0 with the main weapon (-6 with the off-hand).

Proficient (1 slot): The penalties are reduced: off-hand damage penalty becomes -1, Armor Class penalty becomes -1, and THAC0 penalties are reduced to -2 with the main weapon and -4 with the off-hand.

Specialized (2 slots): All penalties to Armor Class, and main weapon combat rolls are removed.

Master (3 slots): The off-hand damage penalty is removed, THAC0 penalty with the off-hand is reduced to -2, and the wielder gains a +1 bonus to Armor Class.


